subSubSection.paragraph:
Aphaereta basirufa
Granger 1949
: 405; 
Shenefelt 1974
: 957; 
Fischer 1994
: 773; 
Yu et al. 2012
.

This species is similar to 

Aphaereta
sarcophagensis

Shenefelt, 1974 from South Africa, but differs in having the first metasomal tergite paler than second and third tergites (similar colouration in 
Aphaereta sarcophagensis
), hind femur 5.0-5.5 times as long as its maximum width (4.5 times in 
Aphaereta sarcophagensis
), first flagellar segment 3.7-4.0 times as long as its maximum width (3.0 times in 
Aphaereta sarcophagensis
); second segment 5.0-5.6 times (4.6 times in 
Aphaereta sarcophagensis
); third segment 4.5 times (3.3 times in 
Aphaereta sarcophagensis
), face twice as wide as high (1.6 times in 
Aphaereta sarcophagensis
), and clypeus 2.4-3.0 times as wide as high (3.5 times in 
Aphaereta sarcophagensis
).
